{
  "texts": [
    "Still, it does not use the verification procedure while providing medical data.",
    "Also, according to their architecture, adversaries can easily change or modify original medical data because they lack the use of encryption processes when transferring data in text format to the controller.",
    "They also implemented attribute-based authentication mechanisms in healthcare system architectures.",
    "Attributedbased authentication denotes the proof of entities such as people in some requirement criteria where a person must have a certain number of attributes, such as a doctor with ten years of experience in heart specialization should be able to access the health data of heart disease patients.",
    "A validator assures that a person owns the required characteristics during the attributed-based authentication and encryption procedure."
  ]
}